National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Ibrahim Kalin, Spokesperson and Chief Advisor to the President of Turkey, to discuss ongoing efforts to prevent further Russian aggression towards Ukraine and de-escalate tensions through diplomacy. They also exchanged views on regional issues, including the situation in Kazakhstan. Both parties emphasized the importance of maintaining stability and unity in Bosnia-Herzegovina, as well as working towards de-escalation and normalization in the Caucasus. Sullivan also highlighted the need to support efforts to end the conflict in Ethiopia.